{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"compliable-stretchy-bee","description":"Block direct commits to `main`/`master` at commit time by enabling the pre-commit\nframework's built-in `no-commit-to-branch` hook, so the \"never commit to main\"\nrule this repo already enforces server-side (GitHub ruleset + Gerrit gates) also\nfails fast locally — at `git commit` instead of only at push/review.\n\n## Why\nCLAUDE.md and CLAUDE.local.md mandate that no change land on `main` except through\nGerrit's two gates. Today nothing stops a local `git commit` while `HEAD` is on\n`main`; the mistake is only caught later at push. Catching it at commit time is\ncheaper and matches the repo's \"errors happen early\" posture.\n\n## What\nAdd the packaged `no-commit-to-branch` hook (id from `pre-commit/pre-commit-hooks`,\nalready pinned at `rev: v6.0.0` in this repo) to the existing hooks list in\n`.pre-commit-config.yaml`. Its default protected set is `master` + `main`, which is\nexactly what we want — no `args:` override needed. Because the repo already depends\non that pinned repo, this adds no new dependency and requires no `rev` bump.\n\n## Scope\n- One file: `.pre-commit-config.yaml`.\n- Add a single `- id: no-commit-to-branch` entry under the existing\n  `- repo: https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit-hooks` block (the one holding\n  `check-yaml`, `check-toml`, etc.).\n- No change to the `local` lint/typecheck hooks; no Makefile change (the hook is\n  activated by the existing `pre-commit install` in `make hooks`).\n- Non-goal: server-side enforcement (already covered by the GitHub ruleset + Gerrit);\n  this is a local fail-fast convenience only, and remains bypassable with\n  `git commit --no-verify` by design.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `.pre-commit-config.yaml` contains a `no-commit-to-branch` hook id under the\n      `pre-commit/pre-commit-hooks` repo block.\n      Proving command: `grep -q 'no-commit-to-branch' .pre-commit-config.yaml && echo OK`\n- [ ] The config still parses and the hook is registered after install.\n      Proving command: `pre-commit run no-commit-to-branch --all-files` exits 0 while\n      on a non-protected branch (the working branch), i.e. it does not error out.\n- [ ] A `git commit` attempted while `HEAD` is on `main` is rejected by the hook.\n      Proving command (non-destructive check on the current worktree, HEAD is on the\n      feature branch so it must PASS there): `pre-commit run no-commit-to-branch\n      --all-files` prints `Passed`; and switching a scratch branch to `main` and\n      running the same hook prints `Failed` (verified manually, not in CI).\n- [ ] Existing gates are unaffected: `make lint && make typecheck` stay green\n      (the config edit is YAML-only, but `check-yaml`/`check-toml` must still pass).\n      Proving command: `pre-commit run --all-files` completes with only expected\n      results (no new failing hook besides an intentional main-branch block test).","id":"e72b-403a-a6ab-4e0c","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Block direct commits to main via pre-commit no-commit-to-branch hook"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784154636280187001,"uuid":"b02d7ffb-b888-47b0-b402-5c04933ba864"}